content: Welcome to Qi Cheng's Homepage Qi Cheng Williams Companies Foundation Presidential Professor Professor of Computer Science University of Oklahoma. A picture Education and CV PhD in Computer Science, University of Southern California, 2001. MSc, Fudan University, China, 1995. BSc, Nankai University, China, 1992. Curriculum Vitae. Research I am interested in theoretical computer science, cryptography, coding theory, computational number theory and molecular computing. We thank National Science Foundation for its support of our research through grants CCF-1900820, CCF-1409294 , CCF-0830524, CCF-0830522 and career award CCR-0237845.
